<subSubSection id="FDE034CE6058B59A726DA87A2007822E" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="14C09D0DCBFCED739257E0D111CB42A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D2E00F362640B54AB4E2FB3C28033D35" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="FF7D79BA39E0755466ED92009EFCDE2D" authorityName="D. G. Zhang, T. Deng &amp; N. Lin" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene sunhangii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sunhangii">
<emphasis id="53C8C35965456F0D96451768E39E3175" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene sunhangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E5BA4559E1C844F6B5C87B1B0E2112BE" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="7BF68FD458D7E5B70B1028732554652E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs through the root tuberous (not cylindric as 
<taxonomicName id="3E8186EAEEF00332385DF1CE1F026535" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="69CADF20989C1238C7269593C5DEA122" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), stems 30-80 cm tall (100 cm tall in 
<taxonomicName id="D31B712996069228E8A19D100EAA5F26" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="A695AA179189E8DCCEAFC70365C20969" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leaves elliptic (not obovate in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EB5781C3CC84E38D727B1FDA899204" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="7E9E6BDEACDE2AA003B0AC18C7FCAAB7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 3-veined (not 3/5 veined in 
<taxonomicName id="C32B0C3B2460B5E09BF5B0CE3264D3C4" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="CB97F3D3202EF57BDE267A5558A88CC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and glabrous (not margin ciliate as 
<taxonomicName id="A3A03FB2978C468CCDEE69DCA73A747D" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="841C18828A6A9D9B391F5D7850A89DA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), flowers 35-40 mm diam. (not 20 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="38596085920987C6ED1B4A44972FED0E" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="902BCB97DDEC4FA9B4D4988EF656F647" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), petals purple to red (not white or pale red in 
<taxonomicName id="88687CCAEBCF4B66538CF090567986BC" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="629C0ECE177DFC0C2DC298077B25F7A3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), catacorolla tasseled (not elliptic or linear in 
<taxonomicName id="2199A43B9B5B1EB8A101092715457BD6" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="D79E49E842650B29C8C774C7F651C14D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lobe limbs divided to 1/3 (more than 1/3 in 
<taxonomicName id="F1314B71DDFBEE02253F72A502A51157" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="D831819949725AA514386837FC8980BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="429CEF7F14FF03ACBE00B155549319C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="01A3300D4D1891087F70F3292C7A2987" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29A3A6540CFC1D17CDBBCCABB9EACC75" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
Herbs perennial. Plant with densely ciliate, tuberous roots and dichasial cymose inflorescences containing many flowers. Stems diffuse, 30-80 cm tall, much-branched, pubescent. Leaves elliptic, 4-10 
<normalizedToken id="EC287825381BDA33B4BE36E1B28F9D6A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-5 cm, glabrous, conspicuously 3-veined. Pedicel 20-30 mm long, pubescent. Calyx tubular-clavate, ca. 1.5-2 cm long, densely hairy on veins; teeth triangulate, ciliate. Petals pale purple to red, ca. 2.5 cm long; claws exserted beyond calyx; catacorolla tasseled, limbs obovate, bifid to 1/3; lobes lanceolate, without a linear lobe or narrow tooth on each side. Stamens slightly exserted; filaments pubescent. Capsule ovoid, 10-20 mm long. Seeds dark brown, reniform, ca. 1 mm long, with lateral auricular pits (
<figureCitation id="995D9714D6E4A74716D0A6D23893A846" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Silene sunhangii (from the holotype plant). A plant habit B plant C leaf D flower E calyx F open capsule. Scale bar: 20 cm (A, B), 1 cm (C, D, E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362528" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="97EC7B0E76046A295EB36ACD48FEA7CC" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. 1 - 5 Silene platyphylla Franchet (modified from illustration in flora of China), 6 - 10 Silene sunhangii, 1, 6 flowering branch 2, 7 sterile branch 3, 8 petal and stamen 4, 9 pistil 5, 10 root." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362529" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure3">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
