<paragraph id="4EFAD396744CD55470A15B4BF1E68E60" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Flowering occurs from February to April, and fruiting from April to June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F059E64B4C59AE71D6FBA2FF2D7258F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A719173703D94B0CE9749ACFFD826265" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0254C055E9BE6AE575E9262B3DC60C" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">The new species is named in honor of Chinese botanist, Prof. Hang Sun, who has made significant contributions to the flora of China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08EF86B294425B1F272A0EA6A3C64E76" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3B636FBE74A6B9B2E7CAC2D306B9E07F" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Distribution, habitat and conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CECB538757C228A2F4D71088A7EF40CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="CB1982E7E6282D1867BFFA73BFDE1953" authorityName="D. G. Zhang, T. Deng &amp; N. Lin" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene sunhangii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sunhangii">
<emphasis id="803C39BD9E03C07BB0E3DFBB17B618AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene sunhangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is presently known from only Hubei and Hunan provinces in central China (
<figureCitation id="44469B0DB60A5B682E3CEE594382490F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of Silene sunhangii. The black dots represent locations of S. sunhangii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362527" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). It grows in humid and evergreen or deciduous mixed forest, from 1214-2227 m (
<figureCitation id="7608AAF5F7F11A09CEA6D81D7332629A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of Silene sunhangii. The black dots represent locations of S. sunhangii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362527" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" tableDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.135.36426.figure1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). A total of three natural populations have been located, each comprising less than 100 individuals distributed over an area not exceeding 100 m2. These populations are located within the Shennongjia National Nature Reserve (Hubei province), Houhe Nature Reserve (Hubei Province) and Huping Mountains (Hunan Province), and are therefore well-protected; there are no known threats to these populations. Further field studies are needed to more authoritatively determine the geographic range and frequency of this species. In the meantime, current evidence indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="AA6182298EB4805F16F815D5CEE2DAF4" authorityName="D. G. Zhang, T. Deng &amp; N. Lin" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene sunhangii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sunhangii">
<emphasis id="1CF666AC0349313D820F564F50C622A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene sunhangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be assigned the conservation status of &quot;Data Deficient (DD)&quot;, following the IUCN Red List Criteria and Categories (
<bibRefCitation id="11E730F24AE38596CD087AEA27263C05" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Bioinformatics (Oxford, England)" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B5" refString="IUCN, 2017. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 108 pp. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 108 pp." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2017">IUCN 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5DB754080ABB29D2139B7C5F750C4EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="F78E07A342F358D51485FF8468E50A27" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11213886E856F6A6330D0975AB189497" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="F39FACF5F7CD9AF94A153F2F578166EE" authorityName="D. G. Zhang, T. Deng &amp; N. Lin" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene sunhangii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sunhangii">
<emphasis id="CD38AB72590E012F4217AE0B6412A908" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene sunhangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a perennial with densely ciliate, tuberous roots and dichasial cymose inflorescences containing many flowers. These characters indicate that the new species should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="E7308F1A482A88920E4EB1A16695B6DE" authority="subsect. Silene" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Cucubaloideae" subsection="Silene">Silene sect. Cucubaloideae subsect. Silene</taxonomicName>
Chowdhuri. It can be distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="74CDE0F666CD72A9E664CE429DBD725B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3D2CC9B9DC8E08C134AF67174440208D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that possess lilac to red petals through its root, stem, leaf and corolla characters as described above. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="28E5CD4EA6290EEAFE2CA60BFBF44F38" authorityName="D. G. Zhang, T. Deng &amp; N. Lin" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene sunhangii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sunhangii">
<emphasis id="2DAF5CACE1C0BEC35D2F9CE45C0437A3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene sunhangii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows greatest similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="C3EBC6AE9ADA8A9C3C8A53EABF0683B0" genus="S." lsidName="S. platyphylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="5F933BA07C60632369669316E4CE6037" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The diagnosis above enables the two species to be reliably distinguished. 
<taxonomicName id="671FC5477B4C97B2FD6CEC2D706D3C7A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene platyphylla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyphylla">
<emphasis id="6416C988E53A4116AF55577659E1AF90" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Silene platyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in western Yunnan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
